{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":720,"text":"There are a few things\nthat all of us need."},{"time":5800,"text":"We all need air to breathe."},{"time":9320,"text":"We need clean water to drink."},{"time":11720,"text":"We need food to eat.\nWe need shelter and love."},{"time":14760,"text":"You know. Love is great, too."},{"time":18360,"text":"And we all need a safe place to pee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21880,"text":"(Laughter) Yeah?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23680,"text":"As a trans person who doesn't fit neatly\ninto the gender binary,"},{"time":27640,"text":"if I could change the world tomorrow"},{"time":31040,"text":"to make it easier for me to navigate,"},{"time":33080,"text":"the very first thing I would do"},{"time":35320,"text":"is blink and create single stall,\ngender-neutral bathrooms"},{"time":40280,"text":"in all public places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42960,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":49600,"text":"Trans people and trans issues,"},{"time":51680,"text":"they've been getting a lot\nof mainstream media attention lately."},{"time":55640,"text":"And this is a great and necessary thing,"},{"time":58400,"text":"but most of that attention\nhas been focused"},{"time":60880,"text":"on a very few individuals,"},{"time":63320,"text":"most of whom are kinda rich"},{"time":65760,"text":"and pretty famous,"},{"time":67400,"text":"and probably don't have to worry that much\nanymore about where they're going to pee"},{"time":71360,"text":"in between classes\nat their community college,"},{"time":73560,"text":"or where they're going to get changed\ninto their gym strip"},{"time":76320,"text":"at their public high school."},{"time":77720,"text":"Fame and money insulates\nthese television star trans people"},{"time":84400,"text":"from most of the everyday challenges"},{"time":87280,"text":"that the rest of us\nhave to tackle on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94200,"text":"Public bathrooms."},{"time":97200,"text":"They've been a problem for me\nsince as far back as I can remember,"},{"time":101720,"text":"first when I was just a little baby tomboy"},{"time":105440,"text":"and then later as a masculine-appearing,\npredominantly estrogen-based organism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111160,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112240,"text":"Now, today as a trans person,\npublic bathrooms and change rooms"},{"time":117160,"text":"are where I am most likely\nto be questioned or harassed."},{"time":122080,"text":"I've often been verbally\nattacked behind their doors."},{"time":125600,"text":"I've been hauled out by security guards\nwith my pants still halfway pulled up."},{"time":130360,"text":"I've been stared at,\nscreamed at, whispered about,"},{"time":132760,"text":"and one time I got smacked in the face\nby a little old lady's purse"},{"time":137520,"text":"that from the looks of the shiner\nI took home that day"},{"time":140120,"text":"I am pretty certain contained at least\n70 dollars of rolled up small change"},{"time":143920,"text":"and a large hard candy collection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148800,"text":"And I know what some of you are thinking,"},{"time":152800,"text":"and you're mostly right."},{"time":155600,"text":"I can and do just use the men's room\nmost of the time these days."},{"time":162840,"text":"But that doesn't solve\nmy change room dilemmas, does it?"},{"time":167520,"text":"And I shouldn't have to use the men's room\nbecause I'm not a man."},{"time":173960,"text":"I'm a trans person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176200,"text":"And now we've got\nthese fearmongering politicians"},{"time":180080,"text":"that keep trying to pass\nthese bathroom bills."},{"time":182280,"text":"Have you heard about these?"},{"time":183640,"text":"They try to legislate\nto try and force people like myself"},{"time":186440,"text":"to use the bathroom\nthat they deem most appropriate"},{"time":191160,"text":"according to the gender\nI was assigned at birth."},{"time":193720,"text":"And if these politicians\never get their way,"},{"time":197240,"text":"in Arizona or California or Florida"},{"time":200760,"text":"or just last week in Houston, Texas,"},{"time":203160,"text":"or Ottawa,"},{"time":204880,"text":"well then, using the men's room\nwill not be a legal option for me either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211880,"text":"And every time one of these politicians\nbrings one of these bills to the table,"},{"time":215619,"text":"I can't help but wonder, you know,"},{"time":217680,"text":"just who will and exactly how would we\ngo about enforcing laws like these. Right?"},{"time":224240,"text":"Panty checks?"},{"time":225920,"text":"Really."},{"time":227600,"text":"Genital inspections outside\nof bath change rooms at public pools?"},{"time":234200,"text":"There's no legal\nor ethical or plausible way"},{"time":238200,"text":"to enforce laws like these anyway."},{"time":242600,"text":"They exist only to foster fear"},{"time":245160,"text":"and promote transphobia."},{"time":249320,"text":"They don't make anyone safer."},{"time":252400,"text":"But they do for sure make the world\nmore dangerous for some of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256480,"text":"And meanwhile, our trans children suffer."},{"time":259880,"text":"They drop out of school,\nor they opt out of life altogether."},{"time":264440,"text":"Trans people, especially trans\nand gender-nonconforming youth"},{"time":269400,"text":"face additional challenges\nwhen accessing pools and gyms,"},{"time":273880,"text":"but also universities,"},{"time":276600,"text":"hospitals, libraries."},{"time":280160,"text":"Don't even get me started\non how they treat us in airports."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285920,"text":"If we don't move now"},{"time":288800,"text":"to make sure that these places"},{"time":291440,"text":"are truly open and accessible to everyone,"},{"time":294520,"text":"then we just need to get honest"},{"time":297640,"text":"and quit calling them public places."},{"time":301800,"text":"We need to just admit"},{"time":304680,"text":"that they are really only open for people"},{"time":307520,"text":"who fit neatly\ninto one of two gender boxes,"},{"time":313600,"text":"which I do not."},{"time":316720,"text":"I never have."},{"time":320240,"text":"And this starts very early."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323400,"text":"I know a little girl.\nShe's the daughter of a friend of mine."},{"time":327440,"text":"She's a self-identified tomboy."},{"time":330840,"text":"I'm talking about cowboy boots"},{"time":332960,"text":"and Caterpillar yellow toy trucks\nand bug jars, the whole nine yards."},{"time":337760,"text":"One time I asked her\nwhat her favorite color was."},{"time":340240,"text":"She told me, \"Camouflage.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":342560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":345680,"text":"So that awesome little kid,"},{"time":347840,"text":"she came home from school last October"},{"time":350680,"text":"from her half day of preschool"},{"time":352960,"text":"with soggy pants on because the other kids\nat school were harassing her"},{"time":357040,"text":"when she tried to use the girls' bathroom."},{"time":360000,"text":"And the teacher had already instructed her\nto stay out of the boys' bathroom."},{"time":365320,"text":"And she had drank two glasses\nof that red juice"},{"time":368880,"text":"at the Halloween party,"},{"time":370360,"text":"and I mean, who can resist\nthat red juice, right? It's so good."},{"time":375680,"text":"And she couldn't hold her pee any longer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379400,"text":"Her and her classmates\nwere four years old."},{"time":382640,"text":"They already felt empowered enough"},{"time":385720,"text":"to police her use\nof the so-called public bathrooms."},{"time":392440,"text":"She was four years old."},{"time":393760,"text":"She had already been taught\nthe brutal lesson"},{"time":396880,"text":"that there was\nno bathroom door at preschool"},{"time":401240,"text":"with a sign on it\nthat welcomed people like her."},{"time":406400,"text":"She'd already learned that bathrooms\nwere going to be a problem,"},{"time":410760,"text":"and that problem started with her"},{"time":414560,"text":"and was hers alone."},{"time":418840,"text":"So my friend asked me\nto talk to her little daughter,"},{"time":422520,"text":"and I did."},{"time":424560,"text":"I wanted to tell her"},{"time":427080,"text":"that me and her mom\nwere going to march on down"},{"time":429290,"text":"and talk to that school,\nand the problem was going to go away,"},{"time":432240,"text":"but I knew that wasn't true."},{"time":433640,"text":"I wanted to tell her that it was all\ngoing to get better when she got older,"},{"time":437480,"text":"but I couldn't."},{"time":440240,"text":"So I asked her to tell me\nthe story of what had happened,"},{"time":445600,"text":"asked her to tell me how it made her feel."},{"time":449400,"text":"\"Mad and sad,\""},{"time":452760,"text":"she told me."},{"time":454880,"text":"So I told her"},{"time":456760,"text":"that she wasn't alone"},{"time":459000,"text":"and that it wasn't right\nwhat had happened to her,"},{"time":461400,"text":"and then she asked me\nif I had ever peed in my pants before."},{"time":467040,"text":"I said yes, I had,"},{"time":469760,"text":"but not for a really long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472680,"text":"Which of course was a lie,"},{"time":475040,"text":"because you know\nhow you hit, like, 42 or 43,"},{"time":477800,"text":"and sometimes you just,\nI don't know, you pee a little bit"},{"time":480800,"text":"when you cough or sneeze,"},{"time":482080,"text":"when you're running upstairs,\nor you're stretching."},{"time":485280,"text":"Don't lie."},{"time":486840,"text":"It happens. Right?"},{"time":488600,"text":"She doesn't need to know that, I figure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493720,"text":"I told her, when you get older,\nyour bladder is going to grow bigger, too."},{"time":499160,"text":"When you get old like me,"},{"time":500440,"text":"you're going to be able\nto hold your pee for way longer,"},{"time":504400,"text":"I promised her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507160,"text":"\"Until you can get home?\""},{"time":510200,"text":"she asked me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512720,"text":"I said, \"Yes,"},{"time":516240,"text":"until you can get home.\""},{"time":520280,"text":"She seemed to take some comfort in that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526800,"text":"So let's just build some single stall,\ngender-neutral bathrooms"},{"time":532600,"text":"with a little bench for getting changed\ninto your gym clothes."},{"time":536880,"text":"We can't change the world overnight"},{"time":540400,"text":"for our children,"},{"time":541640,"text":"but we can give them\na safe and private place"},{"time":544120,"text":"to escape that world,"},{"time":545600,"text":"if only for just a minute."},{"time":550200,"text":"This we can do."},{"time":553280,"text":"So let's just do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555840,"text":"And if you are one of those people\nwho is sitting out there right now"},{"time":559160,"text":"already coming up with a list of reasons\nin your head why this is not a priority,"},{"time":563200,"text":"or it's too expensive,"},{"time":565360,"text":"or telling yourself that giving\na trans person a safe place to pee"},{"time":569000,"text":"or get changed in"},{"time":570680,"text":"supports a lifestyle choice\nthat you feel offends your morality,"},{"time":576600,"text":"or your masculinity,"},{"time":578800,"text":"or your religious beliefs,"},{"time":580280,"text":"then let me just appeal"},{"time":582560,"text":"to the part of your heart\nthat probably, hopefully,"},{"time":587000,"text":"does care about\nthe rest of the population."},{"time":591760,"text":"If you can't bring yourself\nto care enough about people like me,"},{"time":597920,"text":"then what about women and girls"},{"time":600240,"text":"with body image issues?"},{"time":602800,"text":"What about anyone\nwith body image stuff going on?"},{"time":607360,"text":"What about that boy at school\nwho is a foot shorter than his classmates,"},{"time":613000,"text":"whose voice still hasn't dropped yet? Hey?"},{"time":616880,"text":"Oh, grade eight,"},{"time":618840,"text":"what a cruel master you can be."},{"time":622040,"text":"Right?"},{"time":623800,"text":"What about people with anxiety issues?"},{"time":627960,"text":"What about people with disabilities\nor who need assistance in there?"},{"time":631560,"text":"What about folks with bodies\nwho, for whatever reason,"},{"time":635080,"text":"don't fit into the mainstream idea\nof what a body should look like?"},{"time":639520,"text":"How many of us still feel shy"},{"time":642640,"text":"or afraid to disrobe\nin front of our peers,"},{"time":646200,"text":"and how many of us allow that fear"},{"time":648800,"text":"to keep us from something as important"},{"time":652080,"text":"as physical exercise?"},{"time":657200,"text":"Would all those people not benefit"},{"time":660720,"text":"from these single stall facilities?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":665040,"text":"We can't change\ntransphobic minds overnight,"},{"time":671240,"text":"but we can give everybody"},{"time":674240,"text":"a place to get changed in"},{"time":678080,"text":"so that we can all get to work"},{"time":681880,"text":"making the world safer"},{"time":684800,"text":"for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687640,"text":"Thank you for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691160,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692400,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}